    0,\n    \"m_Type\": \"UnityEditor.ShaderGraph.StickyNoteData\",\n    \"m_ObjectId\":
    \"252e69ac4f0943b7a30cc5bd36ed5f53\",\n    \"m_Title\": \"2. Perlin noise\",\n   
    \"m_Content\": \"In Unity's ShaderGraph, Perlin noise is generated via a Gradient
    Noise node. Create that and another float parameter Perlin Scale, which we will
    feed into the Scale pin of the Gradient noise node. Then, use a Remap node to
    modify the output distribution of Perlin to (-1, 1). Do this by setting the input
    bounds to (0, 1) and the output bounds to (-1, 1). Multiply the output by another
    new float parameter Distort Amplitude.\",\n    \"m_TextSize\": 0,\n    \"m_Theme\":
    0,\n    \"m_Position\": {\n        \"serializedVersion\": \"2\",\n        \"x\":
    -1114.666748046875,\n        \"y\": -407.3333435058594,\n        \"width\": 854.0,\n       
    \"height\": 100.0\n    },\n    \"m_Group\": {\n        \"m_Id\": \"\"\n    }\n}\n\n{\n   
    \"m_SGVersion\": 0,\n    \"m_Type\": \"UnityEditor.ShaderGraph.BlockNode\",\n   
