    \"643bf576d1c246c2b5c6cc7527aa838d\",\n    \"m_Title\": \"6. Forgetting anything?\",\n   
    \"m_Content\": \"Our normals are still flat! Fortunately, we can solve this problem
    in 1 step: create a Normal From Height node, and feed it the output of PolygonGradient
    (our height map). Go ahead and forward the output to the Normal output of the
    Fragment shader: our sand material is done!\",\n    \"m_TextSize\": 0,\n    \"m_Theme\":
    0,\n    \"m_Position\": {\n        \"serializedVersion\": \"2\",\n        \"x\":
    2151.33349609375,\n        \"y\": 748.0,\n        \"width\": 460.66650390625,\n       
