    \"m_SGVersion\": 0,\n    \"m_Type\": \"UnityEditor.ShaderGraph.StickyNoteData\",\n   
    \"m_ObjectId\": \"7b1c334ead9242f38b296659b74a596f\",\n    \"m_Title\": \"5.
    Height map -> Color\",\n    \"m_Content\": \"We finally have a nice enough height
    map modeling our dunes. Let's add one last feature to model the grainy appearance
    of sand.\\nCreate a Simple Noise node: this will generate uniform noise. Multiply
    it by a small constant (such as 0.2) and sum it to the output of PolygonGradient.
    Then, pass the result through a Saturate node to ensure its values lie in [0;1].
    \\nAs we did previously, create a Sample Gradient node and select two different
    shades of sand colors at t = 0 and t = 1. Feed the output of Saturate into the
    Time pin of Sample Gradient. That's it for our color: you may forward the output
    to the Base Color of the Fragment Shader.\",\n    \"m_TextSize\": 0,\n    \"m_Theme\":
    0,\n    \"m_Position\": {\n        \"serializedVersion\": \"2\",\n        \"x\":
    337.0,\n        \"y\": 190.0,\n        \"width\": 821.0,\n        \"height\":
    110.0\n    },\n    \"m_Group\": {\n        \"m_Id\": \"\"\n    }\n}\n\n{\n   
    \"m_SGVersion\": 0,\n    \"m_Type\": \"UnityEditor.ShaderGraph.BlockNode\",\n   
