    \"m_SGVersion\": 0,\n    \"m_Type\": \"UnityEditor.ShaderGraph.StickyNoteData\",\n   
    \"m_ObjectId\": \"b914c18f3f4544a2ac53487288bf190a\",\n    \"m_Title\": \"3.
    UV editing\",\n    \"m_Content\": \"In order to make our material more customizable,
    we will allow for a) rotating the UV domain and b) smoothly repeating the UV
    map along the vertical axis.\\nFirst, create a Rotate node and feed the output
    of step 1 into its UV pin. Create a new float parameter Rotation and feed it
    into the Rotation pin. Split the output vector. Now, we will multiply its second
    component by 2 * PI * Sine Frequency, another float parameter that we will now
    add. To obtain 2 * PI, use a Constant node and select TAU. \\nFinally, feed the
    output of the multiplication into a Sine node.\",\n    \"m_TextSize\": 0,\n   
    \"m_Theme\": 0,\n    \"m_Position\": {\n        \"serializedVersion\": \"2\",\n       
    \"x\": -1361.0,\n        \"y\": 758.0,\n        \"width\": 529.0,\n        \"height\":
    156.0\n    },\n    \"m_Group\": {\n        \"m_Id\": \"\"\n    }\n}\n\n{\n   
    \"m_SGVersion\": 0,\n    \"m_Type\": \"UnityEditor.ShaderGraph.TilingAndOffsetNode\",\n   
