    \"625978f30ef1493aa747e0a8d1c240b5\",\n    \"m_Title\": \"5. Interpolation\",\n   
    \"m_Content\": \"Create a Smoothstep node. This performs Hermite interpolation,
    similarly to Lerp: however, here we specify the range and the return is always
    between 0 and 1. \\nWe will plug 0 into the Edge1 pin, our Edge Width parameter
    into the Edge2 pin, and we will use z (computed in 4) as our interpolant. Plug
    the Out pin of Smoothstep into the subgraph output pin.\",\n    \"m_TextSize\":
    0,\n    \"m_Theme\": 0,\n    \"m_Position\": {\n        \"serializedVersion\":
    \"2\",\n        \"x\": 1058.0,\n        \"y\": 30.000003814697267,\n        \"width\":
    451.11767578125,\n        \"height\": 160.0000457763672\n    },\n    \"m_Group\":
    {\n        \"m_Id\": \"\"\n    }\n}\n\n{\n    \"m_SGVersion\": 0,\n    \"m_Type\":
